## [FAIL] MEDIUM — TitleBlock `marginBottom` prop removed from type but relied upon in "no-lead" no-grid-cover case

**What the spec says:**
A3d shows `type TitleBlockProps = { title: string; marginTop: number; centered?: boolean; }` — no `marginBottom`. The inline-style shows `marginBottom: props.marginBottom ?? 0`, implying default is 0 when not passed. For no-grid-cover: `<TitleBlock title={...} marginTop={...} centered />` — no `marginBottom` passed. Comment: "Body folgt mit eigenem top-margin".

**What the current code has:**
Current `kind === "text" && isFirst` branch passes `marginBottom={meta.lead ? TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP : TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP}` to TitleBlock. For the no-lead case, this is `TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP = 64px`. This is the entire gap between the Title and the first body block.

**What a developer will implement:**
After removing `marginBottom` from TitleBlock (following the spec's type definition), and NOT passing it in the no-grid-cover branch, the `marginBottom` of the TitleBlock div becomes 0. The gap between Title and Body relies entirely on "body's own top-margin" — which is an undocumented invariant never stated in the spec. If body blocks don't have an intrinsic top-margin (likely — they probably relied on TitleBlock's marginBottom for spacing in this branch), the Title sits flush against the first body block. This is a visual regression for items with no lead text.

**E5 does NOT catch this:** E5 smoke says "No-Grid-Path: Eintrag OHNE Bilder öffnen → Slide 1 = Title + Lead zentriert" — this assumes lead IS present. There is no E5 scenario for "item with no lead text, no grid".

**Impact:** Visual regression on valid item type (no lead, no grid). Not caught by any automated test or E5 smoke as currently written.

**Fix:** Either (a) add `TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP_NO_LEAD_COVER` constant and explicitly show `<TitleBlock ... marginBottom={meta.lead ? 0 : TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP} centered />` in the no-grid-cover JSX, OR (b) add an E5 smoke case: "Eintrag OHNE Lead-Text, OHNE Bilder → Slide 1 = Title zentriert, Body beginnt mit ~64px Abstand".

