## [FAIL] LOW — `parseImageCount` cleanup left as "Implementer prüft via grep"

**What the spec says:**
A6e says: "Die Function `parseImageCount` selbst BLEIBT in der Datei (möglicherweise von anderem Code aufgerufen — Implementer prüft via grep; falls kein anderer Aufrufer: Function-Body entfernen)."

**What is actually true:**
`parseImageCount` in `instagram-layout/route.ts` has exactly one call site: the `?images=` parameter extraction that A6 replaces with inline logic. No other callers exist. The function is guaranteed dead code after A6.

**Risk:** If the developer doesn't grep and leaves the function in place, ESLint `no-unused-vars` (if configured — project uses ESLint 9) will warn. More likely: TypeScript with `noUnusedLocals` might fail `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit`. Even if linting passes, Codex would flag an unused private function as P3.

**Fix:** Replace "Implementer prüft via grep" with: "`parseImageCount` in `instagram-layout/route.ts` hat keinen anderen Aufrufer — ist dead code nach A6e. MUSS entfernt werden."

